{
  "stem": "19969.4",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 105.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "One of them-- I did talk with the prisoners and say, what did you get to eat?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Well, they said, we got a cup of coffee in the morning and a piece of bread in the evening.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "This was at the last.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Apparently, years before they had treated them much better.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But in the last year of the war, Germany itself was running out of food so they were getting almost no-- nothing to eat at all and malnutrition was extreme.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They say hardly anyone weighed over 95 pounds.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And of course, the resistance went down and typhus was endemic.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And even after we-- in a couple of days, we had two Army hospitals before I left-- before my battalion left, two Army hospitals came up and they immediately started taking care of prisoners.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We did not have any responsibility except as guards.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Well, they immediately took over the care of the prisoners and they died at the rate of, I don't know, 50 to 75 a day for the first week or so after those two hospitals got there.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They were just too far gone.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They could did nothing for them. so they kept dying like 50, 75, 100 a day for about the first week until with food and medicine, most of them eventually recovered.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the situation in there, the conditions were just beyond belief.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No sanitation, utter cruelty.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were-- had what they call the roll call square.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That's where all the dead bodies were that we saw inside the camp when we first came up and that's where they assembled the prisoners.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "If anybody tried to-- violated the rules or anything, everybody in the camp had to turn out.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "For 24 hours they had to stand in that roll call square.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
